Cover Page[]

Oni Child Yamato's Golden Harvest Surrogate Pilgrimage Vol. 2 "I want to travel throughout Wano!! Like Oden did!!"

Short Summary[]

While there is seven minutes left before the broadcast begins, the other members of the Five Elders have arrived at Egghead and have all utilized their Zoan abilities. Beginning their attack, Nusjuro disables the Pacifistas, allowing the Marines to focus on eliminating Bonney. Meanwhile after being contacted through a Den Den Mushi with an update, Jinbe, locates Zoro and Lucci, where after hearing Sanji's insult, Zoro quickly attacks Lucci. Meanwhile, Luffy is devoured by Ju Peter, but is saved by Dorry and Brogy.

Long Summary[]

The Five Elders' arrival is noticed by everyone on the island as the battle rages on. In the video, Dr. Vegapunk finishes preparing coffee using one of his new inventions, though it only took about three minutes, so there are seven minutes left until the broadcast officially begins. Dr. Vegapunk even says that if anyone tried to silence his broadcast, that amount of extra time will not be enough to stop it.

The Elders appear before Luffy as their names and forms are revealed: Jaygarcia Saturn is a gyūki; Marcus Mars, an itsumade; Topman Warcury, a fengxi; Ethanbaron V. Nusjuro, a bakotsu; and Shepherd Ju Peter, a sandworm.

Immediately, Nusjuro sees the Pacifista attacking the Marines and changes into his hybrid form, where he gallops at breakneck speed, slashing the cyborgs. Because he moved so fast, the Marines under attack did not see him at all, though reports of a large horse running around and taking down the Pacifista were all over the Marines' radios. To the Marines' surprise, the Pacifista have not been cut, but partially frozen, thereby rendering them immobile. Soon, half of the Pacifista are incapacitated, which the Marines celebrate over because now they can resume their hunt for Bonney.

Mars takes to the sky and starts attacking the Frontier Dome while Sanji tries desperately to get in contact with his crew so he can tell them to escape ASAP. Once he does so, Usopp informs him that they understand they need to escape, but Zoro is still fighting Lucci. Thankfully, they have reunited with Brook and Lilith on board the Thousand Sunny, which Usopp stopped using Midori Boshi: Take Jave Rin. Meanwhile, Saturn, Warcury, and Ju Peter start fighting Luffy, with Ju Peter diving under the ground. Jinbe is still trying to reach Zoro and says he will drag him back by force if necessary.

Speaking of, Zoro gets one of his swords knocked out of his hand by Lucci, who tries to tempt him to abandon the fight by investigating the powerful Haki that popped up when the Five Elders arrived. Jinbe finally reaches Zoro's location where he tells Sanji that he is still fighting. This prompts Sanji to call Zoro a burden for taking his time fighting, and when Zoro overhears Sanji's words, he decides to finish the fight using a move called Three Sword Style: Kokoba Madara Gari, finally taking down Lucci.

As for Luffy, Ju Peter appears from underneath him and swallows him whole. However, Dorry and Brogy finally arrive on the scene and decapitate Ju Peter, freeing Luffy. Luffy is surprised to see the giants again as they tell him they got tired of waiting for him to show up in Elbaph, so they decided to come pick him up instead.

Quick References[]

Chapter Notes[]

  • There are 7 minutes left until the start of Vegapunk's broadcast.
  • The Five Elders are now fully gathered at Egghead and undergo their Zoan Devil Fruit transformations.
    • Jaygarcia Saturn is a gyuki, an ox-spider hybrid yōkai.
    • Marcus Mars is an itsumade, a reptilian bird yōkai.
    • Topman Warcury is a fengxi, a four-tusked boar demon.
    • Ethanbaron V. Nusjuro is a bakotsu, a skeletal horse yōkai.
    • Shepherd Ju Peter is a sandworm, a gigantic desert worm.
  • Nusjuro immobilizes most of the rogue Pacifista units.
    • Nusjuro is confirmed to possess Armament Haki.
  • Vice-Admiral Doberman orders the Marines to prioritize Jewelry Bonney as their target.
  • Mars flies towards the Labophase and hits the Frontier Dome.
    • Sanji alerts the other Straw Hat Pirates to immediately flee the Labophase.
    • Usopp was able to stop the Thousand Sunny from sliding off the edge with one of his Pop Greens, allowing Brook and Lilith to rejoin his group.
  • Roronoa Zoro attacks Rob Lucci, concluding their fight.
  • Dorry and Brogy rescue Luffy by decapitating Ju Peter's beast form.

Trivia[]

  • The full double page spread of the Five Elders is the first full page double spread since Chapter 800, which came out almost nine years before Chapter 1110.
  • Dorry and Brogy saving Luffy from being eaten by St. Shephard Ju Peter is similar to when Dorry saved Luffy from being eaten by Brontosaurus in Chapter 116.
